Goal:¶

The goal of the report is to train our models using linear regression. We will be training models for following variables:

  • median income
  • population
  • number of households

Graph 1 Review (Median income vs Median house value):¶

In this graph, we can see that:

  • Median house value is capped to 500,000 which means that all house values greater than this are taken as 500,000.
  • Almost 80% of the data points lie within the range of 0-10 median_income

Conclusion:¶

The linear regression applied to graph 1 is not ideal however it is better than model 2 and model 3 fit. The prediction made for graph 2 and 3 is bad. E.g in graph 2, median house value greater than 250,000 will always be predicted 200,000 or lesser by the model
